{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775862644233,"sessionID":"ses_2865ac011ffelk50aBJsTPRuP2","part":{"id":"prt_d79a97e06001ehOMy5oDpfSqZs","messageID":"msg_d79a9765a0010I4K6nGqSrK7KI","sessionID":"ses_2865ac011ffelk50aBJsTPRuP2","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775862646840,"sessionID":"ses_2865ac011ffelk50aBJsTPRuP2","part":{"id":"prt_d79a98359001T7kB8XlTKNgibF","messageID":"msg_d79a9765a0010I4K6nGqSrK7KI","sessionID":"ses_2865ac011ffelk50aBJsTPRuP2","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_26c177c66257493eac247d85","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md","offset":100,"limit":200},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n100:     proxy: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"-p\", \"--proxy\", help=\"Custom proxy URL for dependency resolution\"),\n101:     cloud_provider: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--cloud-provider\", help=\"Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei)\"),\n102:     output: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--output\", help=\"Output path for build artifacts\"),\n103:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n104: ) -> None:\n105: ```\n106: \n107: **Version Increment**: Increments `metadata.version` (patch bump for X.Y.Z, or append .1 / fallback {version}-1) before build and reverts on failure.\n108: \n109: ### 2.4 publish Command\n110: \n111: Publishes/deploys using provider `agentcube` (AgentRuntime CR) or `k8s` (Deployment + NodePort Service).\n112: \n113: ```python\n114: def publish(\n115:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\"),\n116:     version: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--version\", help=\"Semantic version string (e.g., v1.0.0)\"),\n117:     image_url: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-url\", help=\"Image repository URL\"),\n118:     image_username: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-username\", help=\"Username for image repository\"),\n119:     image_password: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-password\", help=\"Password for image repository\"),\n120:     description: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--description\", help=\"Agent description\"),\n121:     region: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--region\", help=\"Deployment region\"),\n122:     cloud_provider: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--cloud-provider\", help=\"Cloud provider name\"),\n123:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' or 'k8s'\"),\n124:     node_port: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--node-port\", help=\"NodePort (30000-32767)\"),\n125:     replicas: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--replicas\", help=\"Number of replicas\"),\n126:     namespace: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--namespace\", help=\"Deployment namespace\"),\n127:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n128: ) -> None:\n129: ```\n130: \n131: ### 2.5 invoke Command\n132: \n133: POSTs JSON to the published agent endpoint.\n134: \n135: ```python\n136: def invoke(\n137:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\"),\n138:     payload: str = typer.Option(\"{}\", \"--payload\", help=\"JSON-formatted input passed to the agent\"),\n139:     header_list: Optional[List[str]] = typer.Option(None, \"--header\", help=\"Custom HTTP headers\"),\n140:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' or 'k8s'\"),\n141:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n142: ) -> None:\n143: ```\n144: \n145: **Header Format**: Headers are parsed as `key:value` format. Invalid format prints error and exits with code 1.\n146: \n147: **Session Header**: If metadata contains `session_id`, adds header `X-Agentcube-Session-Id` to request.\n148: \n149: ### 2.6 status Command\n150: \n151: Loads workspace metadata and displays agent status in a Rich `Table`.\n152: \n153: ```python\n154: def status(\n155:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\"),\n156:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' or 'k8s'\"),\n157:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n158: ) -> None:\n159: ```\n160: \n161: **Exit Codes**: Exits with code 1 when status is `not_published` or `error`.\n162: \n163: ## 3. Runtime Classes\n164: \n165: ### 3.1 PackRuntime\n166: \n167: Handles workspace validation, metadata loading/creation, Dockerfile generation.\n168: \n169: ```python\n170: class PackRuntime:\n171:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n172:     def pack(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n173:     def _validate_workspace_structure(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n174:     def _load_or_create_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n175:     def _apply_option_overrides(self, metadata: AgentMetadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n176:     def _validate_language_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n177:     def _validate_python_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n178:     def _validate_java_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n179:     def _process_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n180:     def _generate_dockerfile(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Optional[Path]: ...\n181: ```\n182: \n183: ### 3.2 BuildRuntime\n184: \n185: Manages Docker image build process with local and cloud modes.\n186: \n187: ```python\n188: class BuildRuntime:\n189:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n190:     def build(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n191:     def _increment_version(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata) -> Any: ...\n192:     def _validate_build_prerequisites(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n193:     def _build_local(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n194:     def _build_cloud(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n195: ```\n196: \n197: ### 3.3 PublishRuntime\n198: \n199: Handles deployment to AgentCube or Kubernetes.\n200: \n201: ```python\n202: class PublishRuntime:\n203:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None: ...\n204:     def publish(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n205:     def _publish_cr_to_k8s(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n206:     def _publish_k8s(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n207:     def _prepare_image_for_publishing(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str: ...\n208: ```\n209: \n210: ### 3.4 InvokeRuntime\n211: \n212: Handles agent invocation via HTTP.\n213: \n214: ```python\n215: class InvokeRuntime:\n216:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None: ...\n217:     def invoke(self, workspace_path: Path, payload: Dict[str, Any], headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None) -> Any: ...\n218:     async def _invoke_agent_via_agentcube(self, agent_id: str, payload: Dict[str, Any], headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]], endpoint: str, workspace_path: Path) -> Any: ...\n219:     async def _direct_http_invocation(self, endpoint: str, payload: Dict[str, Any], headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]], workspace_path: Path) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n220: ```\n221: \n222: **Known Issue**: `_invoke_agent_via_agentcube` may raise `UnboundLocalError` if `endpoint` doesn't start with `http`.\n223: \n224: ### 3.5 StatusRuntime\n225: \n226: Retrieves and displays agent status.\n227: \n228: ```python\n229: class StatusRuntime:\n230:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None: ...\n231:     def get_status(self, workspace_path: Path, provider: Optional[str] = None) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n232:     def _get_k8s_status(self, metadata) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n233:     def _get_cr_k8s_status(self, metadata) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n234: ```\n235: \n236: ## 4. Services\n237: \n238: ### 4.1 DockerService\n239: \n240: ```python\n241: class DockerService:\n242:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n243:     def check_docker_available(self) -> bool: ...\n244:     def build_image(self, dockerfile_path: Path, context_path: Path, image_name: str, tag: str = \"latest\", build_args: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n245:     def get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n246:     def push_image(self, image_name: str, registry_url: Optional[str] = None, username: Optional[str] = None, password: Optional[str] = None) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n247:     def remove_image(self, image_name: str) -> bool: ...\n248: ```\n249: \n250: ### 4.2 MetadataService\n251: \n252: ```python\n253: class MetadataService:\n254:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n255:     def load_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n256:     def save_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n257:     def update_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, updates: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n258:     def validate_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path) -> bool: ...\n259: ```\n260: \n261: **Metadata File**: Saved to `{workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml` using `yaml.dump` with `default_flow_style=False`, `indent=2`.\n262: \n263: ### 4.3 KubernetesProvider\n264: \n265: ```python\n266: class KubernetesProvider:\n267:     def __init__(self, namespace: str = \"default\", verbose: bool = False, kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None) -> None: ...\n268:     def deploy_agent(self, agent_name: str, image_url: str, port: int, entrypoint: Optional[str] = None, replicas: int = 1, node_port: Optional[int] = None, env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n269:     def wait_for_deployment_ready(self, name: str, timeout: int = 120) -> None: ...\n270:     def get_agent_status(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n271:     def delete_agent(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n272: ```\n273: \n274: ### 4.4 AgentCubeProvider\n275: \n276: ```python\n277: class AgentCubeProvider:\n278:     def __init__(self, namespace: str = \"default\", verbose: bool = False, kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None) -> None: ...\n279:     def deploy_agent_runtime(self, agent_name: str, image_url: str, port: int, entrypoint: Optional[str] = None, env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None, workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None, router_url: Optional[str] = None, readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = None, readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = None) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n280:     def get_agent_runtime(self, name: str, namespace: str) -> Optional[Dict[str, Any]]: ...\n281: ```\n282: \n283: **CR API**: `group=\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"`, `version=\"v1alpha1\"`, `plural=\"agentruntimes\"`.\n284: \n285: ## 5. Data Models\n286: \n287: ### 5.1 AgentMetadata (Pydantic BaseModel)\n288: \n289: | Field | Type | Default | Description |\n290: |-------|------|---------|-------------|\n291: | `agent_name` | str | (required) | Unique name identifying the agent |\n292: | `description` | Optional[str] | None | Human-readable summary |\n293: | `language` | str | \"python\" | Programming language used |\n294: | `entrypoint` | str | (required) | Command to launch the agent |\n295: | `port` | int | 8080 | Port exposed by the agent runtime |\n296: | `build_mode` | str | \"local\" | Build strategy: local or cloud |\n297: | `region` | Optional[str] | None | Deployment region |\n298: | `version` | Optional[str] | None | Semantic version string for publishing |\n299: | `image` | Optional[Dict[str, Any]] | None | Container image information |\n\n(Showing lines 100-299 of 1155. Use offset=300 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"    proxy: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"-p\", \"--proxy\", help=\"Custom proxy URL for dependency resolution\"),\n    cloud_provider: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--cloud-provider\", help=\"Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei)\"),\n    output: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--output\", help=\"Output path for build artifacts\"),\n    verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n) -> None:\n```\n\n**Version Increment**: Increments `metadata.version` (patch bump for X.Y.Z, or append .1 / fallback {version}-1) before build and reverts on failure.\n\n### 2.4 publish Command\n\nPublishes/deploys using provider `agentcube` (AgentRuntime CR) or `k8s` (Deployment + NodePort Service).\n\n```python\ndef publish(\n    workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\"),\n    version: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--version\", help=\"Semantic version string (e.g., v1.0.0)\"),\n    image_url: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-url\", help=\"Image repository URL\"),\n    image_username: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-username\", help=\"Username for image repository\"),\n    image_password: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-password\", help=\"Password for image repository\"),","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md","time":{"start":1775862646830,"end":1775862646838}}}}
