{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775862658360,"sessionID":"ses_2865ac011ffelk50aBJsTPRuP2","part":{"id":"prt_d79a9b037001LfrAcI4FZ9Zf3E","messageID":"msg_d79a9a5ee001jW1bPsVEMLBgTW","sessionID":"ses_2865ac011ffelk50aBJsTPRuP2","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_a6a683b873c54303a4136c54","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md","limit":200,"offset":950},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n950: | 409 | Conflict | Resource already exists |\n951: | 422 | UnprocessableEntity | Validation failed |\n952: | 429 | TooManyRequests | Rate limit exceeded |\n953: | 500 | InternalServerError | Internal server error |\n954: | 502 | BadGateway | Upstream unavailable |\n955: | 503 | ServiceUnavailable | Service temporarily unavailable |\n956: | 504 | GatewayTimeout | Upstream timeout |\n957: \n958: ### 4.2 Error Response Format\n959: \n960: ```json\n961: {\n962:   \"error\": {\n963:     \"code\": 404,\n964:     \"message\": \"Resource not found\",\n965:     \"details\": {\n966:       \"resource\": \"AgentRuntime\",\n967:       \"name\": \"my-agent\",\n968:       \"namespace\": \"default\"\n969:     }\n970:   }\n971: }\n972: ```\n973: \n974: ### 4.3 Common Errors\n975: \n976: | Error | HTTP Code | Retry | Resolution |\n977: |-------|-----------|-------|------------|\n978: | SandboxNotFound | 404 | No | Check name/namespace |\n979: | DeletionFailed | 500 | Yes | Check K8s cluster state |\n980: | StaleFinalizer | 500 | No | Manual cleanup required |\n981: | OrphanedResource | 500 | Yes | Force delete |\n982: | ResourceNotFound | 404 | No | Resource already deleted |\n983: \n984: ## 5. Testing Strategy\n985: \n986: ### 5.1 Unit Tests\n987: \n988: Each binary should have unit tests for:\n989: - Configuration parsing\n990: - Flag handling\n991: - Error cases\n992: \n993: ```go\n994: // Example: router configuration test\n995: func TestRouterConfig(t *testing.T) {\n996:     tests := []struct {\n997:         name    string\n998:         flags   []string\n999:         wantErr bool\n1000:     }{\n1001:         {\n1002:             name:    \"valid config with required flags\",\n1003:             flags:   []string{\"--workload-manager-url\", \"http://localhost:8080\"},\n1004:             wantErr: false,\n1005:         },\n1006:         {\n1007:             name:    \"missing required flag\",\n1008:             flags:   []string{},\n1009:             wantErr: true,\n1010:         },\n1011:     }\n1012:     \n1013:     for _, tt := range tests {\n1014:         t.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n1015:             // Test configuration parsing\n1016:         })\n1017:     }\n1018: }\n1019: ```\n1020: \n1021: ### 5.2 Integration Tests\n1022: \n1023: - End-to-end binary startup tests\n1024: - K8s client integration tests (requires test cluster)\n1025: - Store integration tests (requires Redis/Valkey)\n1026: \n1027: ### 5.3 Build Verification\n1028: \n1029: ```bash\n1030: # Build all binaries\n1031: go build -o bin/agentd ./cmd/agentd\n1032: go build -o bin/picod ./cmd/picod\n1033: go build -o bin/router ./cmd/router\n1034: go build -o bin/workload-manager ./cmd/workload-manager\n1035: \n1036: # Verify binaries exist and are executable\n1037: ls -la bin/\n1038: ```\n1039: \n1040: ## 6. Dependencies\n1041: \n1042: ### 6.1 Go Module Dependencies\n1043: \n1044: ```\n1045: github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube          # Main module\n1046:   ├── k8s.io/api                          # K8s API types\n1047:   ├── k8s.io/apimachinery                 # K8s utilities\n1048:   ├── k8s.io/client-go                   # K8s client\n1049:   ├── k8s.io/klog/v2                     # Logging\n1050:   ├── k8s.io/controller-runtime          # Controller framework\n1051:   ├── github.com/gin-gonic/gin            # HTTP framework\n1052:   ├── github.com/redis/go-redis/v9        # Redis client\n1053:   ├── github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go      # Valkey client\n1054:   ├── github.com/prometheus/client_golang # Metrics\n1055:   └── github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5       # JWT support\n1056: ```\n1057: \n1058: ### 6.2 External Dependencies\n1059: \n1060: | Component | Requirement | Description |\n1061: |-----------|-------------|-------------|\n1062: | Kubernetes | ≥1.24 | K8s API server |\n1063: | Redis/Valkey | ≥6.0 | Session store |\n1064: | Docker | Optional | For building agent images |\n1065: \n1066: ## 7. Configuration Precedence\n1067: \n1068: Configuration is loaded in the following order (later overrides earlier):\n1069: \n1070: 1. Default values (hardcoded)\n1071: 2. Environment variables (`AGENTCUBE_*`)\n1072: 3. Config file (`/etc/agentcube/config.yaml`)\n1073: 4. Command-line flags\n1074: \n1075: ### 7.1 Environment Variables\n1076: \n1077: | Variable | Binary | Description |\n1078: |----------|--------|-------------|\n1079: | `AGENTCUBE_KUBECONFIG` | all | Path to kubeconfig |\n1080: | `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` | all | Default namespace |\n1081: | `AGENTD_METRICS_ADDR` | agentd | Metrics address |\n1082: | `ROUTER_WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | router | Backend URL |\n1083: | `ROUTER_STORE_ADDRESS` | router | Redis/Valkey address |\n1084: | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_STORE_ADDRESS` | workload-manager | Store address |\n1085: | `PICOD_WORKSPACE` | picod | Workspace directory |\n1086: \n1087: ### 7.2 Config File Format\n1088: \n1089: ```yaml\n1090: # /etc/agentcube/config.yaml\n1091: apiVersion: v1\n1092: kind: AgentCubeConfig\n1093: metadata:\n1094:   name: agentcube\n1095: spec:\n1096:   namespace: default\n1097:   session:\n1098:     timeout: 15m\n1099:     maxDuration: 8h\n1100:   store:\n1101:     type: redis\n1102:     address: localhost:6379\n1103:     password: \"\"\n1104:   router:\n1105:     listenAddress: \":8080\"\n1106:     workloadManagerURL: \"http://localhost:8081\"\n1107:   workloadManager:\n1108:     listenAddress: \":8081\"\n1109: ```\n1110: \n1111: ## 8. Deployment\n1112: \n1113: ### 8.1 Docker Images\n1114: \n1115: Each binary is packaged as a separate Docker image:\n1116: \n1117: ```dockerfile\n1118: # For agentd, router, workload-manager\n1119: FROM golang:1.24-alpine AS builder\n1120: WORKDIR /build\n1121: COPY go.mod go.sum ./\n1122: RUN go mod download\n1123: COPY . .\n1124: RUN CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=linux go build -o /agentd ./cmd/agentd\n1125: \n1126: FROM alpine:3.19\n1127: RUN apk --no-cache add ca-certificates\n1128: COPY --from=builder /agentd /agentd\n1129: ENTRYPOINT [\"/agentd\"]\n1130: ```\n1131: \n1132: ### 8.2 Kubernetes Deployment\n1133: \n1134: The system can be deployed using Helm:\n1135: \n1136: ```yaml\n1137: # values.yaml\n1138: agentd:\n1139:   enabled: true\n1140:   replicas: 1\n1141:   \n1142: router:\n1143:   enabled: true\n1144:   replicas: 2\n1145:   service:\n1146:     type: NodePort\n1147:     port: 80\n1148:     \n1149: workloadManager:\n\n(Showing lines 950-1149 of 1155. Use offset=1150 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"| 409 | Conflict | Resource already exists |\n| 422 | UnprocessableEntity | Validation failed |\n| 429 | TooManyRequests | Rate limit exceeded |\n| 500 | InternalServerError | Internal server error |\n| 502 | BadGateway | Upstream unavailable |\n| 503 | ServiceUnavailable | Service temporarily unavailable |\n| 504 | GatewayTimeout | Upstream timeout |\n\n### 4.2 Error Response Format\n\n```json\n{\n  \"error\": {\n    \"code\": 404,\n    \"message\": \"Resource not found\",\n    \"details\": {\n      \"resource\": \"AgentRuntime\",\n      \"name\": \"my-agent\",\n      \"namespace\": \"default\"\n    }","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md","time":{"start":1775862658348,"end":1775862658356}}}}
